From 829472bd0c6b73e55f7aa2cf57f806b2393f1201 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Basti <89860334+Xerolux@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 3 May 2026 13:10:34 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] Upgrade paho-mqtt 1.6.1 to 2.1.0

Migrate from paho-mqtt 1.6.1 to paho-mqtt >=2.1.0.
In paho-mqtt 2.0+, mqtt.Client() requires CallbackAPIVersion
as first argument.

Changes:
- requirements.txt: paho_mqtt==1.6.1 -> paho-mqtt>=2.1.0
- mqtt.Client('id') -> mqtt.Client(mqtt.CallbackAPIVersion.VERSION1, client_id='id')
- mqtt.Client() -> mqtt.Client(mqtt.CallbackAPIVersion.VERSION1)
- 8 files changed (broker, smarthome/mqtt, smartcommon, remoteSupport, simpleAPI)

Tested on Debian Trixie (Python 3.13.5) with openWB2 service running.
Requires-Python: >=3.7 (compatible with Python 3.9+)
